West African Inflation Accelerates to 3.9% in March

-- B y   E m i l y   B o w e r s
-- 
2011-06-01T11:36:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/west-african-inflation-accelerates-to-3-9-in-march-correct-.html
(Corrects figure in headline to 3.9 percent.)  Inflation in the eight-member West
African Economic and Monetary Union accelerated to 3.9 percent
in March from 3.7 percent a month earlier, the group said today.  The inflation rate in  Ivory Coast , the biggest economy in
the union, was the highest at 5.8 percent while Burkina Faso
recorded the lowest at 1.3 percent, according to a statement on
